<subSubSection id="C42198270AD975D1A7E579A36B09492E" pageId="18" pageNumber="111" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9B253AD9F6403AF6986A2C4D0F57083E" pageId="18" pageNumber="111">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE6F3FF7FA5DEC170D3F7A064DDDAD8D" pageId="18" pageNumber="111">
For a long time, 
<taxonomicName id="E1B2D647E85CE28F6B07BA507627367F" authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1886" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella vernicosa" order="Selaginellales" pageId="18" pageNumber="111" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="vernicosa">
<emphasis id="2ED081B7109B5A03D59164D736E1B405" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="111">Selaginella vernicosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was thought to occur only in Venezuela (
<bibRefCitation id="A995167F98E2090F53418E552F3A6C3D" author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany" pageId="19" pageNumber="112" pagination="233 - 330" refId="B2" refString="Alston, AHG, Jermy, AC, Rankin, JM, 1981. The genus Selaginella in tropical South America. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Botany 9: 233 - 330" title="The genus Selaginella in tropical South America." volume="9" year="1981">Alston et al. 1981</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A28E83AF962485AB26C399F43B07D8BA" author="Smith, AR" journalOrPublisher="Pteridophytes, Spermatophytes: Acanthaceae-Araceae" pageId="21" pageNumber="114" pagination="296 - 314" refId="B25" refString="Smith, AR, 1995. Selaginellaceae. Pteridophytes, Spermatophytes: Acanthaceae-Araceae Vol. 2: 296 - 314" title="Selaginellaceae." volume="Vol. 2" year="1995">Smith 1995</bibRefCitation>
), but 
<bibRefCitation id="639C4320D7354477E516FB9E1DFA330F" author="Cremers, G" editor="Funk, V" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the United States National Herbarium" pageId="19" pageNumber="112" pagination="17 - 56" refId="B4" refString="Cremers, G, Hickey, RJ, Lellinger, DB, Mickel, JT, Moran, RC, Ollgaard, B, Smith, AR, 2007. Pteridophytes &amp; allies. In: Funk, V, Hollowell, T, Berry, P, Kelloff, C, Alexander, SN, Eds., Checklist of the plants of the Guiana Shield (Venezuela: Amazonas, Bolivar, Delta Amacuro; Guyana, Surinam, French Guiana). Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 55: 17 - 56" title="Pteridophytes &amp; allies." volume="55" volumeTitle="Checklist of the plants of the Guiana Shield (Venezuela: Amazonas, Bolivar, Delta Amacuro; Guyana, Surinam, French Guiana)." year="2007">Cremers et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
reported it recently from Guyana, a report that needs to be confirmed. Its range is also here documented in Brazil.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E6986BAEFA2E9C652E92D8CB0DEA618" pageId="18" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName id="E1CE0112B41DB907700500145D28D2F3" authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1886" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella vernicosa" order="Selaginellales" pageId="18" pageNumber="111" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="vernicosa">
<emphasis id="7AEB4DE5DDA083CF2824E80292469AA1" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="111">Selaginella vernicosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most distinct by its ascending to erect habit, coriaceous, strongly imbricate and shiny leaves due to waxy deposits, the median leaves ovate to ovate-deltate with the midribs raised or prominent, with short-ciliate margins at least along proximal ⅔, otherwise dentate on distal ⅓, carinate, acute apices, lateral leaves ovate-deltate with acroscopic margins short-ciliate along proximal 
<normalizedToken id="F30D57EBD653277D2592C0CD7A10C3BB" originalValue="½">1/2</normalizedToken>
, otherwise dentate distally, and basiscopic margins ciliate along proximal 
<normalizedToken id="44CD15277B262CAE71C74F27F7A18A67" originalValue="¼-½">1/4-1/2</normalizedToken>
, otherwise entire distally with the apices entire or tipped by a tooth.
</paragraph>
